16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
18 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 508 of Title 69, unless there is
19 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
20 A. This act shall be known and may be cited as the Evacuation
21 Vehicle Access Corridor Act.
22 B. There is hereby created in the State Treasury a revolving
23 fund for the Oklahoma Department of Transportation to be designated
24 the "Evacuation Vehicle Access Corridor Revolving Fund" or "EVAC
Req. No. 11633 Page 1

1 Fund ". The fund shall be a continuing fund, not subject to fiscal
2 year limitations, and shall consist of all monies directed for
3 deposit to the fund by law. All monies accruing to the credit of
4 said fund are hereby appropriated and may be budgeted and expended
5 by the Oklahoma Department of Transportation in accordance with the
6 provisions provided in Section C of this act. Expenditures from
7 said fund shall be made upon warrants issued by the State Treasurer
8 against claims filed as prescribed by law with the Director of the
9 Office of Management and Enterprise Services for approval and
10 payment.
11 C. 1. There is hereby established the Evacuation Vehicle
12 Access Corridor Grant Program, which may also be cited as the "EVAC
13 Grant Program";
14 2. The Oklahoma Department of Transportation shall establish
15 and administer the EVAC Grant Program to support the state purpose
16 of ensuring the health and safety of the residents of Oklahoma
17 living in geographically landlock basins by creating evacuation
18 corridors. Such program shall embody the following procedures and
19 criteria:
20 a. the Department shall create and make available to
21 counties of the state a standardized Evacuation
22 Vehicle Access Corridor grant application;
23
